# Development Guidelines

Conventions for writing code in softwhere.uz. Follow the layered architecture and the shared infrastructure in `src/core`; do not reintroduce the pre-refactor `utils/api.ts` / `lib/db.ts` / `constants/` / `types/` layout ŌĆö those paths no longer exist.

## At a glance

| Concern | Do this | Source |
| --- | --- | --- |
| DB access | Call a repository; never touch Drizzle/`db` in routes or pages | `src/modules/*/model/*.repository.ts` |
| HTTP calls | Use `apiClient` (or a module's `api` wrapper); check `response.success` | `src/core/http.ts` |
| AI | Call the helpers in `core/ai` (quota-aware, provider fallback) | `src/core/ai.ts` |
| Logging | Use `logger`, not `console.*` | `src/core/logger.ts` |
| Constants | Import from `core/constants` (or a module's `constants.ts`) | `src/core/constants.ts` |
| i18n | `next-intl`; keys in `src/messages/*.json` | `src/core/i18n.ts` |
| Layers | `core` -> `shared` -> `modules` -> `app` (enforced) | `eslint.config.mjs` |

## Layer boundaries

`eslint-plugin-boundaries` enforces the import direction in `eslint.config.mjs`:

```
core   -> core
shared -> core, shared
module -> core, shared, own module (same moduleName)
app    -> core, shared, module, app
```

The rule (`boundaries/element-types`) currently runs at **`warn`** severity, so `yarn lint` stays green while the pre-existing cross-layer couplings noted in the config are surfaced rather than blocking. Do not add new violations. `src/messages/**`, `src/proxy.ts`, `**/global.d.ts`, and `scripts/**` are excluded from the check.

## Data access ŌĆö repository pattern

Only repositories import `@/core/db`. Routes and pages import repository functions, never Drizzle directly.

```typescript
// src/app/api/admin/posts/route.ts
import { createPost, listForAdmin, slugTaken } from '@/modules/blog/model/posts.repository';
import { requireAdmin } from '@/core/auth';
```

The DB is Neon (serverless Postgres) accessed via Drizzle's HTTP driver (`src/core/db.ts`) ŌĆö **not** MongoDB/Mongoose. There is no `MONGODB_URI`; the connection env var is `DATABASE_URL`. Schemas live in `src/modules/blog/model/BlogPost.ts` (`blog_posts`) and `src/modules/contact/model/Lead.ts` (`leads`). Full data-access conventions are in `api-migration.mdc`.

## HTTP calls

Client-side and server-to-internal calls go through `apiClient` from `src/core/http.ts`, which returns a `{ success, data?, error? }` envelope, logs the request, and applies a 10s default timeout:

```typescript
import { apiClient } from '@/core/http';

const res = await apiClient.get<{ post: { slug: string } }>('/api/blog/posts/related?...');
if (res.success) {
  // res.data is present
}
```

Prefer a module's typed wrapper when one exists (`src/modules/blog/api/posts.ts`, `src/modules/estimator/api.ts`) over calling `fetch` inline.

## AI generation

All model calls go through `src/core/ai.ts` (OpenAI-compatible SDK). The chain is **Kimi K2.6 (Moonshot) primary, DeepSeek V4 Pro fallback**, both quota-aware and env-overridable; if only one key is set, that provider is used alone. Use the exported helpers rather than instantiating a client:

- `safeGenerateContent` / `generateContentWithProvider` ŌĆö text (blog bodies get a large token budget + a longer timeout)
- `safeGenerateJSON` / `safeGenerateJSONWithTimeout` ŌĆö JSON output
- `generateWithWebSearch` ŌĆö grounded generation via Moonshot's `$web_search` (Kimi-only)

> Note: some older docs describe AI as "DeepSeek only". The code makes DeepSeek the **fallback**; Kimi K2.6 is the default primary provider.

## Logging

Use the `logger` singleton from `src/core/logger.ts`; `no-console` is a lint warning and the logger is the sanctioned `console` boundary. Include a context tag:

```typescript
import { logger } from '@/core/logger';
logger.error('Neon Auth session check failed', e, 'AUTH');
```

Errors and warnings are always emitted (including in production); info/debug are dev-only.

## Internationalization

`next-intl` with locales `uz` (default), `ru`, `en`. Message catalogs are `src/messages/{uz,ru,en}.json`; request config is `src/core/i18n.ts`; routing/redirect middleware is `src/proxy.ts`. Validate locales with `isValidLocale` / `validateLocale` from `src/core/auth.ts`. Related-locale posts are linked by `generationGroupId`.

## Admin auth

Guard admin route handlers with `requireAdmin` from `src/core/auth.ts`. It authorizes **either** a Neon Auth session whose user has the `admin` role **or** a `Bearer ${API_SECRET}` header (machine callers). Browser admin calls should go through `adminFetch` (`src/modules/admin/utils/adminFetch.ts`), which sends the session cookie and reloads on 401.

## Environment variables

Validated at startup in `src/core/env.ts`. Only `DATABASE_URL` is required; the rest are optional and degrade gracefully.

| Var | Required | Purpose |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `DATABASE_URL` | yes | Neon Postgres connection |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_BASE_URL` | no (defaults to `https://softwhere.uz`) | Base URL for internal calls (`ENV.BASE_URL`) |
| `MOONSHOT_API_KEY` (or `KIMI_API_KEY`) | no | Kimi K2.6 ŌĆö primary AI provider |
| `DEEPSEEK_API_KEY` | no | DeepSeek ŌĆö AI fallback |
| `API_SECRET` | no | Bearer auth for admin/generation endpoints |
| `NEON_AUTH_BASE_URL`, `NEON_AUTH_COOKIE_SECRET` | no | Neon Auth admin login (gate fails closed if unset) |
| `UNSPLASH_ACCESS_KEY` | no | Blog cover images |
| `EXCHANGERATE_API_KEY` | no | Currency rates for the estimator |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_TG_BOT_TOKEN`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_TG_CHAT_ID` | no | Telegram contact-form notifications |

> `env.example` is partially stale: it predates `MOONSHOT_API_KEY`, `NEON_AUTH_*`, and `EXCHANGERATE_API_KEY`. Treat `src/core/env.ts` as the source of truth.

## Avoid

- Importing `@/core/db` / Drizzle anywhere outside a repository.
- `console.*` ŌĆö use `logger`.
- Inline `fetch` when a module `api` wrapper or `apiClient` covers the call.
- `MONGODB_URI`, `src/utils/api.ts`, `src/lib/db.ts`, `src/constants/`, `src/types/` ŌĆö none exist.
- New cross-layer imports that violate the boundary rules.

